
[1]spiral

   SPI'RAL, a. [L. spira, a spire.] Winding round a cylinder or other
   round body, or in a circular form, and at the same time rising or
   advancing forward; winding like a screw. The magnificent column in the
   Place Vendeme, at Paris, is divided by a spiral line into compartments.
   It is formed with spiral compartments, on which are engraved figures
   emblematical of the victories of the French armies. A whirlwind is so
   named from the spiral motion of the air. Water in a tunnel descends in
   a spiral form.
